This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Obama and leaders of Baltic states during a multilateral meeting in Tallinn, Estonia. The leaders discussed the security situation in Europe, particularly in light of the ongoing conflict in Ukraine. They expressed appreciation for the support and leadership of the United States in ensuring the security of the Baltic states and discussed their expectations for the upcoming NATO Summit. They also discussed the importance of supporting Ukraine and other Eastern Partnership countries, as well as the need for increased cooperation on cyber and energy security. The leaders emphasized the importance of the transatlantic bond and the shared values of democracy, human rights, and freedom. President Obama reaffirmed the United States' commitment to the security of the Baltic states and announced plans to bolster the American military presence in Europe. He assured the Baltic leaders that they will never stand alone and that the United States will always stand with them.